metadata.name: 𝔑𝔞𝔯𝔞𝔰𝔦𝔪𝔥𝔞 - ᴛʜᴇ ᴄʀᴇᴀᴛᴏʀ
metadata.description:
𝕹𝖆𝖒𝖊: 
Narasimha - the Creator

𝕱𝖗𝖔𝖒: 
Nowhere and everywhere

𝕮𝖍𝖗𝖔𝖓𝖎𝖈𝖑𝖊: 
~"Hisˌmanɪfɛˈsteɪʃ(ə)n allowed /fɔːm/ and /ʃeɪp/"~


It dreamt, therefore it manifested into shape and form.

A new beginning. Foundation, structure, framework. 

Silhouettes, shapes and figures, shadows of birth.

Thus the Universe was designed!

"I am the Alpha and Omega, the Beginning and the ending. I was, I am and I Will Be"


~"INITIUM - Where it all bɪˈɡɪnsS"~

𝕷𝖔𝖗𝖊: 
Unmoving atop the Pilar of Creation, Narasimha stands vigilant of his fabrication. 
No particular feelings of attachment.
As easily as It dreamt it, It can unmake it.
